(71, 42, 1, 'Unlock the Domain', '<p>First things first, in order to transfer a domain, you&rsquo;d need to check and confirm that the said domain isn&rsquo;t locked. For that, contact your current registrar for details and make sure the &ldquo;Domain Lock&rdquo; is disabled.</p>', NULL, 'Step 1', NULL, 63, 1, '2020-03-12 07:03:10', '2020-05-06 09:14:27', NULL),
(72, 42, 1, 'Get an Authorisation code', '<p>Next up, you&rsquo;d need to get an authorisation code from your current registrar, it is also often referred to as a transfer key or EPP code. Also, in order to carry out the desired task, we&rsquo;d need approval from your domain&rsquo;s Administrative Contact. The request is sent in the form of an e-mail, and your transfer request may be denied in case the e-mail address is invalid on the current domain registration information.</p>', NULL, 'Step 2', NULL, 64, 1, '2020-03-12 07:03:28', '2020-05-06 09:15:09', NULL),
(73, 42, 1, 'Let us Handle the Rest', '<p>Now that you&rsquo;ve provided us with an authorisation code and the &ldquo;Domain Lock&rdquo; on the said domain is disabled, you can sit back and relax while our team handles the rest.</p>', NULL, 'Step 3', NULL, 65, 1, '2020-03-12 07:03:45', '2020-05-06 09:15:51', NULL),
